cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it deals with sentiment analysis in natural language text. It may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories as it involves the use of weights and probabilities to classify text. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category as sentiment analysis is often used in search engines to improve search results. Finally, Cybernetics (cs.CY) is a less likely sub-category as it deals with the study of control and communication in machines and organisms, but it could be relevant if the sentiment analysis is being used to control or communicate with machines.
